data.event: The first settlement occurred at Alexandria Center around 1811.

event.title: 1812, was a minor engagement in which local forces defeated

data.event: The Battle of Cranberry Creek, during the War of 1812, was a minor engagement in which local forces defeated a much larger group of British soldiers and sailors, who attempted to regain supplies and provisions taken earlier by the Americans.
The town was established in 1821 from the Town of Brownville and the Town of Le Ray.

event.title: was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1988

data.event: The Densmore Methodist Church of the Thousand Islands was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1988.
